# ===========================
# gRPC Endpoints
# ===========================
#
# The Peer Service primarily uses gRPC for peer-to-peer communication.
# gRPC endpoints are available on port 5000 using HTTP/2.
#
# Available gRPC Services:
# - PeerDiscoveryService: Peer discovery and network membership
#
# To test gRPC endpoints, use grpcurl or a gRPC client:
#
# List available services:
#   grpcurl -plaintext localhost:5000 list
#
# Describe a service:
#   grpcurl -plaintext localhost:5000 describe sorcha.peer.PeerDiscoveryService
#
# Call a method:
#   grpcurl -plaintext -d '{"peer_id": "peer123"}' localhost:5000 sorcha.peer.PeerDiscoveryService/GetPeers
#
# gRPC Reflection is enabled in development mode for service discovery.
#
# ===========================

